description:
George Grant robbed a mail train in his first successful criminal outing and decided to challenge Superman as next exploit. He used his scientific expertise to create a powerful metal suit of armor that did not stand against the strength of Superman.

Years later he would challenge Superman once again. The improved suit of armor, the help of artificially acquired super strength, and a ray weapon which that could weaken Superman could help Metalo defeat The Man of Steel. The ray depleted Superman's strength and through a regiment of intensive training he restored his strength to his former levels and defeated Grant for the last time.

deck: Llyron is the father of Llyra.
description:
Origin

Llyron is the biological father of the half-Lemurian Llyra. Llyron was captured one day by a ship who was at sea in search for marine life. Rhonda Morris owned an Oceanarium and hoped to capture some of the ocean's animals to put on display and study. Over the course of his imprisonment Llyron and Rhonda fell in love and were married in secret. Llyron would later die defending Rhonda from a shark, but not before he impregnated her with his child. That child would grow up to be Llyra.

Llyron's story share strong resemblance to Namor's parents who met and fell in love similarly.

deck: Rhonda is the mother of Llyra.
description:
Origin

Rhonda Morris is the mother of Llyra the half-Lemurian girl. When Rhonda was younger she was on a ship searching for new marine life she could put on display and study at her Oceanarium. While on the ship the crew netted a Lemurian man by the name of Llyron. Over time the two fell in love and were married in secret. Llyron would later die defending Rhonda against a shark but not before Rhonda was impregnated with his baby. That baby being the girl Llyra.

Rhonda's story bares a strong resemblance to Namor's parents who met and fell in love similarly.
